Went here for a date because we love mexican food. Very unusual for us, but we were really disappointed eating dinner here. It looked amazing from all the pictures, but the reality was: Tacos are alright (7/10 in taste) but very small in size. The "spicy/fiery" guac wasn't spicy at all, so that was false advertising, a complete waste of money. The portion of guac you get is also really small. The drinks really weren't that good also, especially the blue tequila drink. It tasted like salty sea water with blue food coloring. Neither of us could finish it, despite how many tiny sips we forced ourselves to drink throughout the night. It also took 10-15 minutes to get our first drinks despite the place being quiet. And finally, the weird looking quesadilla was packed with so much cheese you literally couldn't taste anything else. We also couldn't finish it even when sharing. Needless to say, when you're leaving drinks and food behind, still a little hungry, kind of sick from trying to forcefully finish a bad drink, and spending ~$90 for two people for dinner, you're not going to get people to come back.

I'm not even sure how to begin this review. We came in today, Cinco de Mayo, and were surprised at how not busy this restaurant was. For the poor service we had, you'd think they were wall to wall full. We arrived at 5:30. At 5:45 a server realized she hadn't even greeted us yet. She tells us she will be right back to take our order. At 6 we still hadn't seen her and finally grabbed someone else to at least bring us waters. For appetizers, the 4 of us ordered salsa and a guacamole. Our server suggested we get 2 guacamole because of the size. The salsa comes out 10 mins later in the tiniest dish. One guacamole comes out 10 mins after that. When our server comes to our table at 6:30, we still don't have our drinks but finally put in our dinner order and reminded her about the 2nd guacamole we had ordered (at her recommendation) which she told us she would check on. Spoiler: our second guacamole never showed and we had to ask her to take it off our bill.  We got our drinks finally but honestly don't know if there was even alcohol in them since my margarita tasted extremely watered down. The table behind us had a similar issue and had to send their cocktails back because the alcohol had been completely forgotten.  When our food order arrived, one of our orders was wrong and included a 3rd taco rather than the side we ordered. The side finally arrived (after a reminder) not that there was a spot on the table for it because every single dirty dish was still there. This wrong order wouldn't have been a huge deal except they then charged us for a taco we didn't order and they never even tried to take back.  Honestly, there are much better places in Chicago when it comes to food, service and atmosphere. I wouldn't waste your time here, unless you have two hours to sit around and wait for food.  One positive: the Baja taco was good. That's about it.

Food was pretty tasty but the service was probably one of the worst I've had at a sit down restaurant.  Went on a Saturday night with a group of 5. We were seated at a table right next to the door, which was not an issue until after briefly sitting there. There is a long red carpet that stretches from inside the entrance, out into the seasonal enclosure. It prevented the door from closing all the way when people kept going in and out. This was when it was still cold out, so it made for an uncomfortable time. When we asked our server if there was anything we could do about the door, she said “No, you can just get up and close it. That’s going to keep happening.” Further inspecting the long rug, it was actually 2 rugs, so we pulled one inside (at most 4 inches) and the door could close fine.  A party larger than us arrived after we did and was served before us.  When another server came around, our party asked if chips and salsa were complimentary, as we had not got any yet. The server scoffed “No!” and immediately walked away. Not sure if it’s the norm in this area to not have complimentary chips and salsa, but for most Mexican fare that is typical. Even so, it wouldn’t be that big of a deal had the server not responded so rudely, as if we had asked to keep the silverware or eat the menus.  Several orders were incorrect. I had ordered a Mushroom taco and an Al Pastor taco. I was brought a Mushroom and Fish. When I notified our server she said “that’s what that is, it’s in the Al Pastor style.” I’ve had hundreds of Al Pastor tacos. This was the only time it was ever something besides pork. Not sure if the waitress just didn’t want to admit fault for putting in a wrong order or what, but she didn’t offer to get me a new one and kept insisting that it was Al Pastor. Maybe she thought I was that dumb that I didn’t know any better? Rather than argue with her I just accepted it.  The food was rather tasty, all things considered. Only quality keeping this from being a 1-star rating. I would give it another chance, but it’s unlikely as there are probably better options in the area.
